cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CE, cs.AI 

This paper discusses retrieval models and their optimization for sponsored search, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also proposes a weighing-based strategy for learning semantic representations, which involves machine learning techniques such as cost-sensitive learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of incorporating or disregarding long-tail pairs, which relates to the economics of advertising (cs.CE) and the optimization of search algorithms (cs.AI).
